00:03:23.220 --> 00:03:28.690
We're all seeing crime scene
and forensic people on the TV

00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:29.430
all the time.

00:03:29.430 --> 00:03:32.570
These are actually pictures
of our students at BU.

00:03:32.570 --> 00:03:37.430
We do use lovely blue lights
as alternate light sources

00:03:37.430 --> 00:03:41.310
to identify where there might
be a blood stain or a semen

00:03:41.310 --> 00:03:43.490
stain or something else.

00:03:43.490 --> 00:03:46.710
People do stand around behind
crime scene tape trying

00:03:46.710 --> 00:03:49.340
to figure out how they're
going to approach whatever's

00:03:49.340 --> 00:03:49.970
going on.

00:03:49.970 --> 00:03:54.720
And that's our field space,
which is over in Holliston.

00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:58.380
And evidence does arrive in
labs in little brown bags

00:03:58.380 --> 00:04:00.820
with evidence tape
